Polish Stocks: Bogdanka, Kernel, Lotos, Orlen Move in Warsaw

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-02-11T17:06:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/polish-stocks-bogdanka-kernel-lotos-orlen-move-in-warsaw.html
  Poland ’s WIG20 Index gained 21.05,
or 0.8 percent, to 2,727.06, trimming this week’s decline to 0.6
percent.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.    Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA  (LWB PW), Poland’s only
publicly traded coal producer, climbed for the first time in
three days, adding 1.5 percent to 118.8 zloty.  Kernel Holding SA 
(KER PW), Ukraine’s second-largest exporter of sunflower oil,
increased as much as 3 percent to 85.8 zloty and closed 0.8
percent higher at 84 zloty. The companies will join the WIG20
Index after the close of trade on March 18, the bourse said late
yesterday.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW), Poland’s biggest oil company, gained
for the first time this week, adding 0.99 zloty, or 2.2 percent,
to 45.9 zloty.  Grupa Lotos SA  (LTS PW), the second-largest
refiner, rose 0.46 zloty, or 1.1 percent, to 40.95 zloty. Brent
crude oil for March settlement climbed 24 cents to $101.11 a
barrel on the London-based ICE Futures Europe exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
